<% content_for :page_header do %>
  <h1 class="center">CurateND Research Data Management</h1>
<% end %>

<article class="about-curatnd">
  <blockquote>
    <p>
    Do you have a grant funded project that requires sharing your data?<br />
    Are you worried about finding your data in 5 or 10 years?<br />
    Do you need to publish your data but you are not sure how?
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <p>
    <a href="https://curate.nd.edu/">CurateND</a> is our new repository solution to support the full life cycle of your data and research to support your data sharing mandates.
    Among its many features, it is designed to facilitate data management implementation, content preservation and secure global sharing of knowledge.
  </p>

  <h3>Deposit It</h3>
  <p>
    CurateND does not care what format of data you are using or the kind files.
    You can store and retrieve any file format or type together, and then share it securely.
    We provide wide preservation support for your content such as datasets, articles, images, whitepapers, and presentations.
  </p>

  <h3>Share It</h3>
  <p>
    Whether privately with your collaborator, with your students, or with the world, CurateND allows you to securely share your work with the right people.
    You can choose private access, campus access, or open access to content.
  </p>

  <h3>Embargo It</h3>
  <p>
    Do you need to preserve your data, but protect it while you have an article, dissertation, or other work in progress?
    No problem.
    You can embargo your data in CurateND until any date in the future, while having the peace of mind your data is already preserved and protected.
  </p>

  <h3>Link It</h3>
  <p>
    Create a DOI for any data links you need to include in an article or paper.
  </p>

  <h3>Cite It</h3>
  <p>
    Once your data is preserved in CurateND with a <abbr title="Digital Object Identifier">DOI</abbr>, your data is citable by others, and your impact accelerates.
  </p>

  <h3>Highlight It</h3>
  <p>
    Highlight your work on your personal profile page.
  </p>

  <h3>Preserve It</h3>
  <p>
    CurateND gives you the peace of mind you can always find your work in the future, and we will migrate content to ensure access and usability.
  </p>

  <h3>Visit Us</h3>
  <p>
    To find out more about what CurateND and library can do for your research data or other digital projects contact <a href="mailto:rick.johnson@nd.edu?subject=CurateND">Rick Johnson</a> or come visit us in the <a href="http://library.nd.edu/">Hesburgh Library&#8217;s</a> <a href="http://library.nd.edu/cds/">Center for Digital Scholarship</a>.
  </p>

</article>
